archive / f10-immunity-challenge Aunder 10/25/2024 12:53 PM # F10: SECRET LOVER 12:57 PM Here's how this will work! In a moment a public challenge chat will open up to all of the players and their loved ones. This is the ONLY place the challenge will be discussed publicly in the game. No tribe chat, no 1on1s, no vcs. You can of course discuss with your loved ones in your confessional. In this chat your goal is discover as many peoples loved ones as possible while hiding who yours is... mostly. 1:01 PM You want 5 of your other cast mates to guess who your loved one is correctly while the other 4 you do not. Here is how scoring will work: For every fellow cast mates loved one you guess correctly, you will gain 1 point The following are the point values you will obtain for each number of people correctly guessing your loved one: 0: 0 points 1: 1 point 2: 3 points 3: 5 points 4: 7 points 5: 10 points 6: 7 points 7: 5 points 8: 3 points 9: 1 point 1:02 PM The tiebreaker will come down to whoever got closest to 5 people guessing their loved one! 1:02 PM Say whatever you must to convince people one way or another, but just remember that all info is for everyone to see! Good luck :) KawaiiQuack 10/25/2024 7:08 PM @snazztastic human beings challenge 7:08 PM !!! KawaiiQuack 10/25/2024 7:16 PM If anyone has questions, ping Aunder because I will probably not have a good answer KawaiiQuack 10/25/2024 7:39 PM Cinnamon and Dreya do not have a loved one, and thus are unable to compete in the challenge and win immunity. (edited) Aunder 10/26/2024 1:37 PM @snazztastic human beings reminder to get your lists in your subs before 7pm est today! KawaiiQuack 10/26/2024 5:44 PM @snazztastic human beings One more reminder, about 75 minutes to get both the challenge and hunt subs in KawaiiQuack 10/26/2024 7:01 PM That's time! Please give us some time to calculate results 1 7:01 PM (When I get back from dinner) (edited) KawaiiQuack 10/26/2024 7:14 PM Results at 7:20 7:20 PM @snazztastic human beings @All Updates hello geeks and gamers apologies for the delay 7:21 PM I will be filling in for your challenge results tonight 7:21 PM Before we get started 7:21 PM 0: 0 points 1: 1 point 2: 3 points 3: 6 points 4: 10 points 5: 6 points 6: 3 points 7: 1 points This is the updated scoring chart, adjusted for the amount of players that participated 7:22 PM Remember, correct guesses earn you one point, while the amount of times you are guessed is determined by the numbers above 7:22 PM So let's get right into it! 7:23 PM Starting with Alba Her loved one was... Gdpaz! three people guessed that, giving Alba 6 points. 7:23 PM Brett, Tyler, and Willow guessed correctly, so they all earn a point. 7:23 PM Speaking of Brett 7:24 PM His loved on was... Kyran! Once again, three people guessed this, giving Brett 6 points. 7:25 PM Wait I lied 7:25 PM Four people guessed it! 7:25 PM So Brett gets 10 points 7:25 PM apologies 7:25 PM Points for Alba, Izzy, Tyler, and Willow 7:26 PM Next up... Izzy B! 7:26 PM Her loved one was Bella 7:26 PM Three people guessed that correctly, giving Izzy 6 points. 7:27 PM And points to Brett, Pigeon, and Willow 7:27 PM LN! His loved one was... 7:27 PM April! 1 7:28 PM Only Willow guessed this correctly, giving them both one point. 7:28 PM Pichu is next 7:28 PM His loved one was Sophia! 7:28 PM Which nobody figured out Well kept secret! 7:28 PM No points 7:28 PM Pigeon's loved one was... MTP 1 1 1 1 1 7:29 PM ! 7:29 PM Only Alba guessed this correctly, earning them each a point 7:29 PM Tyler is next 7:29 PM His loved one was... Sunder! 1 7:29 PM Alba, Brett, LN, and Pigeon all figured this out 7:30 PM Meaning they all get a point, and Tyler hauls a hefty 10. 7:30 PM Leaving Willow, and our final loved one, Hayes! 7:30 PM Pichu correctly put the pieces together 7:30 PM Earning each of them a point 7:30 PM So let's look at the totals! 7:31 PM In 8th place, with 1 point... Pichu 7:31 PM In 7th place with 2 points... LN 7:32 PM In 6th place with 3 points... Pigeon 7:32 PM In 5th place with 5 points... Willow 7:32 PM In 4th place with 7 points... Izzy B 7:32 PM In 3rd place with 9 points... Alba 7:33 PM Leaving Brett and Tyler! The two people with the highest guessed, and recipients of the juicy 10 points. 7:33 PM Winning immunity, in a score of 13 to 12... 7:33 PM @7th-Brett ! Congratulations, you have earned your way into the final 9. Tyler, you came up just short. 7:34 PM Thank you all for playing this admittedly unorthodox challenge, tribal will be set up shortly. archive / f11-immunity-challenge KawaiiQuack 10/22/2024 7:20 PM @snazztastic human beings hello again 7:20 PM Welcome to you're next challenge! 7:21 PM Nah I am kidding, no point in being silly Please go to #mail (again) and stop talking 7:21 PM You have all made the merge! Pilot 10/23/2024 4:01 PM Hello! 4:01 PM Welcome to 4:01 PM # F11 - AMONG US CHALLENGE 4:01 PM 4:02 PM Here's how it works! We're going to simulate 5 separate games of among us at once . And each game will have 2 impostors, randomly chosen, with identities only known to each other. Meaning that all of you (with one exception) will be the impostor in exactly 1 game, and crewmate in the other 4. (1 person will be a crewmate in all 5 games) This challenge will take place over 2 phases, each 12 hours long. (edited) 4:03 PM Each phase you will perform an action in each of the 5 games, depending on whether you are a crewmate or an impostor in that game! 4:04 PM PHASE 1 Crewmate Submit a vote for someone who they believe is the impostor. Choose a location to guard: The options include: Electrical, Reactor, Communications, Med-Bay, and Navigation. Impostor Select a player you would like to kill! They will not be able to participate in phase 2 Submit a vote for someone to be eliminated 4:05 PM Only vote counts, and who is killed will be revealed publicly for each game. The players who are killed along with the player who receive the most votes will not be allowed to participate in phase two for those games. (edited) 4:06 PM PHASE 2 Crewmate Submit a vote for someone who they believe is the impostor. Impostor Choose one location to sabotage! (same options as crewmate to guard) Select a player you would like to kill! Submit a vote for someone who you would like to see eliminated. (edited) 4:08 PM And the end of phase 2: 1. The votes will be revealed, and the person voted out is eliminated from the game 2. If the impostor has not been voted out, they will try to sabotage on of the locations. The sabotage will succeed if no crewmates are guarding the area. 3. If the impostor is still alive, their final kill goes through. (edited) 4:09 PM Points will then be tallied up and annouced 4:09 PM Points are given out as follows for each phase for each game (edited) 4:10 PM Phase 1: Crewmate receives 2 points if they vote for the impostor Crewmate receives 5 points if they are not killed/voted out Impostor receives 4 points if they are not voted out (edited) 4:13 PM Phase 2: Crewmate receives 3 points if they vote for the impostor Crewmate receives 7 points if they are not killed/voted out Impostor receives 6 points if they are not voted out (edited) 4:18 PM After Phase 2: If 2 impostors are alive, both receive 20 points. If 0 impostors are alive, all living crewmates receive 12 points If 1 impostor is alive living crewmates receive 5 points If the sabotage took place successfully, the living impostor(s) receive 30 points (edited) 4:19 PM As an example, I may receive this in my submissions as my assignment: Game 1: Crewmate Game 2: Crewmate Game 3: Impostor with Austin Game 4: Crewmate Game 5: Crewmate My phase one submissions could then look like Game 1: Arvid, Electrical Game 2: Austin, Med-Bay Game 3: Vote: Arvid Kill: Muski Game 4: Quack, Reactor Game 5: Cwis, Reactor And assuming I survive every game, my phase two submission could look like Game 1: Cwis Game 2: Cwis Game 3: Vote Cwis Kill: Quack Sabotage: Electrical Game 4: Austin Game 5: Arvid (edited) 4:20 PM The 2 players who receive the most points will win immunity! Phase 1 starts now, with a deadline at 10/24/2024 7:00 AM Pilot 10/23/2024 7:03 PM @Kireina 7:03 PM You'll be sent your assignments shortly! Pilot 10/23/2024 7:17 PM You may also discuss this challenge as much as you'd like with your tribemates! Pilot The 2 players who receive the most points will win immunity! Phase 1 starts now, with a deadline at 10/24/2024 7:00 AM Pilot 10/23/2024 10:59 PM @Kireina REMINDER PHASE 1 ACTIONS DUE IN 8 HOURS (edited) 11:00 PM You must complete phase 1 to be elligible for phase 2 Pilot 10/24/2024 7:22 AM Here are the round 1 results! 1 7:25 AM Meaning that: Nate, Willow, and Brett die in Game 1 IzzyB, Nate, and Cinnamon die in Game 2 LN, Brett, and Nate die in Game 3 Cinnamon, Dreya, and Pichu die in Game 4 Dreya, Nate, and IzzyB die in Game 5 7:26 AM Round 2 submissions due at 10/24/2024 7:00 PM ! 7:26 AM submit for only the games where you are alive still! Pilot 10/24/2024 6:59 PM Alright @snazztastic human beings Let's get to those results! 1 7:00 PM Starting with the kills and votes from round 2 7:01 PM 1 7:01 PM Thrilling! 7:01 PM Onto how the points actually shake up 7:01 PM In 11th place 7:02 PM Nate, with 28 points 7:02 PM In 10th place 7:02 PM Brett, with 44 points 7:02 PM In 9th place 7:02 PM Dreya, with 54 points 1 7:02 PM In 8th place 7:03 PM Cinnamon, with 72 points 7:03 PM In 7th place 7:03 PM IzzyB, with 82 points 7:03 PM In 6th place 7:03 PM Willow, with 88 points 7:04 PM In 5th place 7:04 PM Ln with 92 points 7:04 PM Onto our top 4 7:04 PM with a reminder that the top 2 scorers will both be immune 7:04 PM In 4th place (edited) 7:04 PM Tyler with 96 points 7:05 PM Meaning that our top 3 is Pichu, Alba, and Pigeon 7:05 PM And guess what? archive / f12-immunity-challenge KawaiiQuack 10/20/2024 6:29 PM Hello gamers For this challenge, we will be doing a Quack classic. Three Monkeys ! So here is how it works: You will need to get into two groups of three. This means one person from @Jax has to sit out, wile one person from @Ilana will have to be a part of both groups. There are three roles. First Monkey: You will be given Google Sheet art. On vc, you must describe the piece to the Second Monkey. Second Monkey: You must transcribe what is being told to you on vc to the Third Monkey over text. You are not allowed to speak to the First Monkey, you must be muted. Third Monkey: You will be given a blank canvas, and are tasked with using the directions from the Second Monkey to try to accurately recreate the art piece. 6:32 PM Your time starts when the Canvas is sent, and ends when you send a link of the completed work and a screenshot of said work. You must use the palette given on the second tab of the sheet. Failure to use the right colors will result in those cells being marked wrong, so be careful! Every incorrectly colored cell will be a five second penalty, meaning if you take 30 minutes but make 10 mistakes, your final time will be 30:50. The tribe with the faster combined time will win immunity! Please note, there are two artworks, one per group. Please ping me with who is doing what, and which group they are apart of (1 or 2). 6:37 PM And one more thing. There is a twist this round. Once again, both tribes are going to tribal, both sets of votes will be read, and the results of this challenge will not be revealed until after. However, the player voted out of the winning tribe will not have immunity at the next cycle. I think that is everything, if you have any questions, please ask! KawaiiQuack 10/20/2024 7:16 PM @snazztastic human beings welcome 7:16 PM Peep the challenge 7:16 PM Peep the twist 7:21 PM Please form your groups as soon as possible! Pilot 10/20/2024 7:25 PM Also, Jax you may not sit out the same person back to back, so @5th-Cinnamon must play 3 KawaiiQuack Your time starts when the Canvas is sent, and ends when you send a link of the completed work and a screenshot of said work. You must use the palette given on the second tab of the sheet. Failure to use the right colors will result in those cells being marked wrong, so be careful! Every incorrectly colored cell will be a five second penalty, meaning if you take 30 minutes but make 10 mistakes, your final time will be 30:50. The tribe with the faster combined time will win immunity! Please note, there are two artworks, one per group. Please ping me with who is doing what, and which group they are apart of (1 or 2). KawaiiQuack 10/21/2024 1:24 AM Unfortunate news Does not change anything for those that already ran it, but the penalty is actually 30 seconds and not 5. Sorry about that! KawaiiQuack 10/21/2024 4:44 PM Hey y'all! Due to some scheduling issues, we're giving an extension to this challenge. Since results are not being revealed tonight anyways, tribal channels will be open at the standard time. So functionally, nothing is changing, but feel free to get this challenge done at your own pace! KawaiiQuack 10/22/2024 7:09 PM @snazztastic human beings @All Updates What's up 2 7:09 PM Time for some results! 7:09 PM I will be snappy I promise 7:10 PM This was our first artwork. 7:10 PM For Jax... we had Tyler, Cinnamon and Pigeon. 7:11 PM All white cells were incorrect 7:11 PM The colored cells are what was correct 7:11 PM Lots of problems! 7:12 PM 327 mistakes 48:58 raw 2:43:30 penalty 3:32:28 total These are the stats 5 7:12 PM Alba, Izzy B, and Pichu did this one for Ilana 7:12 PM This was their success! 7:13 PM 38 mistakes 38:19 raw 19:00 penalty 57:19 total And these are their stats 7:13 PM Ilana takes a commanding lead 7:13 PM This was the second artwork 7:13 PM LN, Willow, and Keira completed this one 7:14 PM And this is what was correct 2 1 7:14 PM 429 mistakes 17:16 raw 3:34:30 penalty 3:51:46 total Stats 1 7:15 PM 7:24:14 is Jax's total time 1 7:15 PM It would take a colossal choke for Ilana to lose this 2 7:15 PM So... did they? 7:15 PM As you can see, they did not! 2 7:15 PM Nearly perfect! 7:16 PM I gotta say, I'm impressed 7:16 PM Truly 7:16 PM 4 mistakes 45:29 raw 2:00 penalty 47:29 total Stats 7:16 PM 1:44:48 is Ilana's total 7:16 PM Meaning... @Ilana wins their first immunity! 1 7:16 PM And now... #mail Exported 38 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

archive / f13-immunity-challenge Dicy 10/18/2024 6:45 PM Final 13 Challenge: Pictionary Framework Today you will be partnering up with-in your tribes to complete a Framework Puzzle, But there's a twist! That twist being you will not have any scrambled words to guide you! Instead of the standard scrambled up words you will be using drawings and a letter bank to solve the words used for the puzzle! In your pair, you need to assign two roles: a "Drawer" and a "Solver" . The goal is to solve a Framework-like puzzle! Here’s how it works: Role Assignment: Once you partnered up and have your roles assigned, please ping us in your tribe chat with the list of pairs and roles! Drawer Responsibilities: The Drawer will run the command ?13-Pictionary-Framework , which will give them ten survivor based words they must illustrate (on their own, no tracing or anything similar) without using any numbers, letters, or words. They will have 15 minutes to complete their drawings. If they take longer than this time limit, their team will be disqualified. (DQ penalty explained in scoring) Solver Responsibilities: Once the Drawer submits all ten drawings, Production will notify the solver. Once the solver is ready, the drawings will be handed over to the Solver. The Solver must then deduce the ten words from the drawings and integrate them into a Framework puzzle. Scoring: The scoring for this challenge will be based on the number of correct answers in the puzzle. In case of a tie, the time taken from when the Solver requests the drawings to the moment the completed puzzle is submitted will serve as the tiebreaker. DQ's For going over the drawing time or A none drawer entering the command will be 1.5x the overall worst time. 6:45 PM 6:45 PM For anyone who is not familiar with a Framework puzzle in general here is an example of a standard Framework puzzle (however you will not get the scrambled words section) 6:45 PM 6:46 PM If you have any questions please ping me! Pilot 10/18/2024 7:27 PM Jax you're sitting someone out btw! Dicy 10/18/2024 8:09 PM Small little note: as a drawer if you are coming up on the 15 time limit you can choose to submit the drawings you have and not give your solver all ten to avoid a DQ. However the solver will only get those done to solve the framework Dicy 10/19/2024 7:01 PM @All Updates @snazztastic human beings I HAVE SOME RESULTS 7:01 PM to start with good news, it didn't end up going to tie breaker! 7:02 PM let us kick things off with what the ten words were to start with 7:02 PM the list of words used for this challenge are: 1.) Fire Making 2.) Final Three 3.) Under the Radar 4.) Buff 5.) Jeff Probst 6.) Rocks 7.) Water Well 8.) Tribal Council 9.) Survivor Auction 10.) Idol 7:03 PM to save time, I will jump right to overall scores and then post a little chart breaking it down after 7:04 PM Winning immunity with a score of 20/30 compared to 10/30...... 7:04 PM @Jax Congrats you have the night off! 7:04 PM meaning @Ilana we will be seeing you at tribal council 7:05 PM as for the induvial pairs scores: 1 7:06 PM (I just realized i flipped those colors on the chart oops) Exported 17 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

funny was that 7:27 PM You probably didnt expect this but 7:27 PM DROP 7:27 PM Nothing? 7:27 PM Sorry for the lies. 7:28 PM But you know what they say 7:28 PM All is fair in love and ORGs 7:28 PM Speaking of, welcome to your next immunity challenge! 7:28 PM F14: All is fair Welcome to your second swap challenge! I hope you've all had time to settle into your tribes. This challenge is a rather simple one. You will be faced with a rotating jigsaw, and that's it! Of course that's not all there is to it. Everyone on each tribe will be doing the puzzle, and the time with the fastest average time wins immunity! How does one stop the other tribe from winning immunity then? Well, with WAR CARDS . These war cards are buffs and debuffs that can be played on your opponent! The 4 war cards are as follows: Doubles time Triples time Halves time Time doesnt count By playing these on your opponent, their time will be altered! If Dicy gets a time of 3:00, but has a triples time card on him, his time becomes 9:00. If Quack were to have a time of 0:30, and the opponents play a "time doesnt count" card, his time won't count towards the average! You pick who to play the cards on as a tribe and there is only one copy of each card per tribe . EVERY CARD NEEDS TO BE PLAYED ONCE The command to get the puzzle is "?f14-love" Make sure to /stopwatch beforehand The tribe that has the fastest time will win immunity and a surefire way to get to F14 7:29 PM If you have any questions, ping prod, I will be asleep :] Armuski F14: All is fair Welcome to your second swap challenge! The 4 war cards are as follows: Doubles time Triples time Halves time Time doesnt count By playing these on your opponent, their time will be altered! If Dicy gets a time of 3:00, but has a triples time card on him, his time becomes 9:00. If Quack were to have a time of 0:30, and the opponents play a "time doesnt count" card, his time won't count towards the average! You pick who to play the cards on as a tribe and there is only one copy of each card per tribe . EVERY CARD NEEDS TO BE PLAYED ONCE The command to get the puzzle is "?f14-love" Make sure to /stopwatch beforehand The tribe that has the fastest time will win immunity and a surefire way to get to F14 Armuski 10/16/2024 7:30 PM If it wasnt clear, the war cards are played as a tribe in your tribes subs channel Armuski 10/16/2024 7:45 PM Please only out your FINAL SUBMISSION in the subs channel. All discussion should be held in tribe chat 7:48 PM You may do the challenge before dealing out war cards Armuski 10/17/2024 10:11 AM Reminder to use the stopwatch command! Armuski used /stopwatch start General Purpose ORG bot BOT 10/17/2024 10:11 AM Stopwatch Started! Note: stopwatch will stop after 1 day. Armuski used /stopwatch stop General Purpose ORG bot BOT 10/17/2024 10:11 AM Stopwatch stopped Time Elapsed 0:00:03.143000 Start Time 10:11:51 AM End Time 10:11:54 AM Timestamps are automatically corrected to your local timezone Armuski 10/17/2024 7:02 PM Grading 7:05 PM @snazztastic human beings 7:05 PM Hello people 7:06 PM Hope you liked jigging AND sawing 7:06 PM Im here to first, reveal the TIMES of everyone 1 7:06 PM Saying this was close would NOT be an overstatement, thats for sure 7:07 PM But it wouldnt be an understatement either. 7:07 PM With a difference by over an hour 7:07 PM 7:07 PM Jax takes the lead 7:07 PM Almost an hour 7:07 PM Oopsies 7:07 PM But... 7:08 PM The heart of the cards, right? 7:08 PM On Jax... 7:08 PM Cinnamon got their time DOUBLED. 7:08 PM Keira had their time TRIPLED 7:09 PM Tyler had his time HALVED 7:09 PM And LN's time doesn't count for the total. 3 7:09 PM On Ilana 7:10 PM Dreya had her time TRIPLED 1 7:10 PM Dar has their time DOUBLED 3 7:10 PM Pichu had their time HALVED 7:10 PM And Izzy B's time is NOT counted. 7:11 PM To those quick on the uptake... 7:11 PM By a difference of 1:47:54 to 2:58:35 7:12 PM @Jax wins their second immunity! 3 7:12 PM 7:13 PM Im letting Pilot do stuff Exported 50 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

archive / f15-immunity-challenge Armuski 10/13/2024 7:22 PM @Kaya @Lilly @All Updates 7:22 PM Hello!! 7:22 PM It's me 7:22 PM Your friendly 1 7:22 PM Swedish production member! 1 1 7:22 PM You see, in Sweden, we have this childhood game, that Ive decided to turn into a challenge for you all 7:23 PM # F15: Vi ska byta lag! 7:23 PM Roughly translated, that means 7:23 PM We're swapping teams 1 1 7:23 PM Now, this sounds 7:23 PM Like a swap 1 7:23 PM Ironically enough 7:24 PM Well too bad 7:24 PM Let me get the write up one sec 7:25 PM For this challenge, I'll need you all to divide into 2 TEAMS with 7 people. Theo will be on neither as he is immune! 7:25 PM Now the twist is 7:25 PM The teams are picked at random 7:25 PM @snazztastic human beings 7:25 PM STOP TALKING IN 1-1S 7:25 PM WERE SWAPPING 7:25 PM OR ALLIANCES 7:25 PM ALL CHATS 7:25 PM #mail 7:25 PM GO GO GO Austin 10/14/2024 7:00 PM Who’s ready for their first Austin challenge!! I’m I hope you all are enjoying your new tribes. Everything nice and cozy? Well now let’s get to our challenge! F15- Welcome to 1-on-1 Battleship with Trivia! This is just a fun game of Battleship…but with a twist! Isn’t that fun? You’ll take turns “firing at the other person’s board,” which is an 8x8 grid. When you call a shot (like “B4”), your opponent will say whether it’s a hit or a miss. If you get a hit, you shoot again! Then, your opponent takes their shot. That’s a round. Every 2 rounds, there will be a trivia question! The first person to answer correctly will get to choose between: • A random hint given by production (3 different types of hints, so your hints will vary). • Two extra shots on their next turn. The first person to sink all of their opponent’s ships wins the battle and gets a point for their tribe! The tribe with the most points after all the 7 1-on-1 battles wins immunity. Best of luck! Ping me with any questions. (edited) 7:03 PM Here is your board https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1F3OG85MFL0KAFsLV0fowX9y69LcaZaahtAbvTVz5XiA/edit F15 Immunity Challenge- Battleship Board- COPY ME!!!! 7:07 PM You will have a 1-on-1 setup with your opponent where prod and Theo will watch you 7:09 PM You will need to find a time with your opponent to do the challenge. It really needs to be run live. You have 24 hours to get it done! (edited) 7:12 PM Your matchups are: Pilot 10/14/2024 7:14 PM @snazztastic human beings Austin 10/14/2024 7:15 PM Send me a copy or photo of your boat placements in your subs Pilot 10/15/2024 2:17 PM Please have your board made and submitted before your start time! (edited) Austin 10/15/2024 7:05 PM Wow 7:06 PM My first challenge is officially over 7:06 PM @snazztastic human beings ready for results? 3 7:07 PM I’ve tallied all the results 7:07 PM I’m gonna say everyone did amazing 7:07 PM Now I’m gonna do something I hate 7:07 PM Long results!!! 7:07 PM 1 by 1 7:08 PM First up we have Derek vs Keira (edited) 7:09 PM Derek made quick work and sunk all 4 of Keira’s boats 7:09 PM Next up 7:09 PM Pichu vs Willow 7:09 PM This one um 7:10 PM This one had some timezone issues but 7:10 PM They got it done 7:10 PM Winning in a very close matchup is 7:10 PM .. 7:10 PM Pichu!!! 7:11 PM Ilana is up 2-0 7:11 PM Next up 7:11 PM We have is 7:11 PM Dar vs Brett 7:13 PM This one wasn’t as close 7:13 PM The winner won more trivia so that might’ve had to do with 7:13 PM Why 7:13 PM … 7:13 PM Brett won! 7:13 PM Jax scores their first point 7:13 PM Next up we have 7:13 PM LN vs Alba 7:14 PM Another close one with both of them only having 1 ship 7:14 PM But in the end 7:15 PM Alba! 7:15 PM Couldn’t come through! 7:15 PM LN gets a point! 7:15 PM We’re all tied up 7:15 PM 2-2 7:15 PM Next up is 7:15 PM Tyler vs Nate 7:16 PM This one come down to the wire 7:16 PM Coming down to a 1 ship each 7:17 PM But the person who was able to fire first was 7:17 PM It was 7:17 PM Tyler 7:17 PM And he hit! 7:17 PM Tyler puts Jax in the lead 7:17 PM 3-2 7:18 PM 2 matchups left 7:18 PM We have 7:18 PM Pigeon vs Izzy 7:18 PM Now 7:18 PM One of these people dominated the trivia 7:18 PM It was 7:18 PM Pigeon 7:18 PM But it didn’t matter because 7:19 PM Izzy sinks Pigeons ships first! 7:19 PM # WE’RE TIED 3-3 7:19 PM Comes down to 7:19 PM # Dreya vs Cinnamon 7:19 PM Our closest battle 7:20 PM Each person only had 1 boat life with only needing 1 more shot to sink 7:20 PM Who was able to get that shot first you ask? 7:20 PM Well…. 7:20 PM It 7:20 PM Was 7:20 PM Cinnamon 7:20 PM Who hits and sinks Dreyas last ship! 7:21 PM # which means Jax has won immunity 7:21 PM # 4-3 7:21 PM I’m sorry Ilana but we will be seeing you at our first tribal of the swap 7:21 PM But 7:21 PM Look on the bright side 7:21 PM Theo gets to join you after tribal! archive / f16-immunity-challenge Pilot 10/11/2024 7:18 PM @snazztastic human beings Hi! 1 7:19 PM Who's ready for your next immunity challenge? 7:20 PM In this challenge, you all will be getting married! 7:20 PM That's right! 7:20 PM Wecome to 7:21 PM # F16 - Newlytribed Game 7:22 PM That's a pretty misleading title... 7:23 PM Welcome to the newlytribed game. Here’s how it works, each of you will be split up into pairs, of your own choosing. Once your partners are chosen, you may not discuss anything related to the challenge with your partner or your will be DQ'd . Then, you will both complete a series of questions, about your partner or your relationship with your partner, so the better you've gotten to know your partnet the better! If you both answer the same answer to the question (or something reasonably close), you will receive a point. The tribe that gets the most points wins! 7:24 PM @Lilly You will be sitting one person out and @Kaya you will be sitting 3 people out (though they can still play if they want to, it just won't count) (edited) 7:24 PM And @13th-Dar must play 7:25 PM Please decide your partners ASAP, and there will be no warning about those DQs, 7:26 PM One last thing... 7:27 PM Both tribes will be attending tribal 7:27 PM This is still a tribal immunity challenge 7:28 PM But we will not be announcing the actual results until both tribes have completed a full tribal cycle, including reading the votes! 7:28 PM Then, only the player from the losing tribe will be eliminated 7:29 PM And just for fun, the player voted out of the winning tribe will be immune for the F15 cycle, regardless of what tribe wins or loses 7:29 PM exciting, right? 5 Pilot 10/12/2024 6:11 PM @snazztastic human beings , everyone has completed the challenge, so we're gonna open up tribal a little early seeing as we're not releasing challenge results rn anyways 6:11 PM You still may NOT discuss your answers with your partner 6:12 PM We will release the results of the challenge after the vote tmrw, till then, enjoy tribal! Pilot 10/13/2024 7:12 PM Hello @Lilly and @Kaya 7:12 PM Let's get to these challenge results shall we Armuski 10/13/2024 7:12 PM It was me I won the challenge 1 Pilot 10/13/2024 7:12 PM First pair from Kaya 7:12 PM Pigeon and Keira 7:13 PM scored.... 1/15 4 2 7:13 PM First pair from Lilly 7:13 PM Tyler and Brett 7:13 PM score... 7:14 PM 5/15 7:14 PM Willow and Dar from Kaya scored... 7:14 PM 4/15 7:14 PM so we are tied up 7:14 PM (though lilly has used one less pair) 7:14 PM Dreya and Nate from Lilly scored... 7:14 PM 4/15 as well 2 7:15 PM that 9 points for Lilly, 5 points for Kaya 1 7:16 PM Derek and IzzyB for Lilly scored... 7:16 PM 8/15 7:16 PM best score so far 7:16 PM meaning Lilly has 17 points! 7:16 PM and Alba and LN need a 13 or higher to win 7:17 PM Alba and LN's score does have a 3 in it... 7:17 PM Sadly, for Kaya, it ONLY has a 3 in it as they got 3/15 7:17 PM Meaning @Lilly wins immunity 7:17 PM Making @16th-Night Our 16th placer and giving @14th-Theo a free pass to at least the final 14! 7:18 PM congrats, next challenge shortly Exported 48 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

Ping prod once your WHOLE TRIBE has decided their pairs. Kaya, since you have 1 extra member someone will be sitting out. question (edited) 7:01 PM And we've elected to use that question as the title of the challenge 7:01 PM # F20 - WHAT WOULD YOU DO FOR 10 POINTS? 2 7:02 PM This challenge will take the form of a scavenger hunt 7:03 PM A submissions channel will be opened up shortly for both tribes, and we will publish a list of items 7:03 PM The items are sorted into 6 categories, and each have a point value between 1 and 10 7:04 PM Each tribe should also make a copy of the google sheet to track their progress 7:04 PM To make a submission, it must be verified by having a sheet of paper with: 1. Your name 2. Your tribe name 3. Tagtreevivor 7:05 PM The tribe with the most points at 7 EST tomorrow will win immunity, the other will be voting the first person out of this game! 7:07 PM Both tribes should have their submissions channels open! 7:07 PM https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1H5RbrKwwJVsb9_Z-pBZD_7IhCMuagjJDaa0Dt-vJnJA/edit?gid=496360468#gid=496360468 Tagtreevivor S2 Scavenger Hunt (Make a copy!) 7:07 PM Here is your scavenger hunt, go nuts! 7:08 PM @All Updates Aunder 10/5/2024 7:11 PM Gl getting 8 points in "On the web" btw :) Pilot 10/5/2024 7:18 PM All animals must be alive 1 KawaiiQuack 10/5/2024 8:46 PM It has come to my attention that someone blacked out the 13R and 13S cells on the score sheet. These keep track of your total score, if y'all wanna see that on your copies, now you know! KawaiiQuack 10/5/2024 8:54 PM (it is missing D12 in the formula btw, might want to add that) KawaiiQuack 10/6/2024 2:56 PM For Impossible Quiz 2, should be clarified, go to 119! And screenshot that Pilot 10/6/2024 7:00 PM Alright @snazztastic human beings Let's go to those results! 7:00 PM We're gonna run through category by category and compare each tribes scores 7:01 PM First off: 7:01 PM Activities 7:01 PM Kaya got a score of... 7:02 PM 48 on the activities category 7:02 PM Lilly got a score of... 7:02 PM 50 on the activities category! 7:03 PM Next, Animals 7:03 PM Kaya got a score of... 7:03 PM 34 on the animals category 7:03 PM Lilly scored... 7:03 PM 12 7:03 PM So that's 82 Kaya, 62 Lilly 7:04 PM Next, prod items ! (edited) 7:04 PM Kaya scored... 7:04 PM 38 (edited) 7:04 PM Lilly scored... 7:04 PM 36 7:05 PM Soooo 120 Kaya, 98 Lilly 7:05 PM For Teamwork 7:05 PM Kaya scored... 7:06 PM 46 7:06 PM And Lilly scored 7:06 PM 21 2 7:06 PM 166 Kaya, 119 Lilly 1 7:06 PM On the web 7:06 PM Kaya scored... 7:07 PM 44 (edited) 7:07 PM Lilly scored... 39 1 7:08 PM That's 210 Kaya, 158 Lilly 7:08 PM With Lilly behind by 52 points, they would need to get almost all the remaining points to win 7:09 PM On interstellar, Kaya scored 7:09 PM 12 7:09 PM For a total of 222 7:09 PM And Lilly scored 7:09 PM 23 7:09 PM For a total score of 181 7:09 PM Which means @Kaya Congratulations , you're immune 7:10 PM And @Lilly you'll be voting the first person out of this game Exported 60 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

archive / f5-immunity-challenge Dicy 11/2/2024 2:49 PM Dicy Challenge part 2, Welcome to your Final 5 Immunity challenge. # F5: Empty Space (edited) Dicy 11/5/2024 4:09 PM For todays Challenge I have created a bit of a puzzle chain for you to solve! There will be three different puzzle types that you will be solving, all that involve filling in the empty space. Once the puzzle is completed you will then use your completed to puzzle to find a hidden code within the puzzle, you will enter those hidden codes into their marked locations on the cover page to reveal the season logo. How you find these "hidden codes" will be clearly marked on each of the puzzles respect google sheet tab. you will know you have the Hidden code correct as a cell will change to a piece of the season logo, if it doesn't you are wrong. I will go ahead and tell you the three puzzle types that will be included in this challenge to allow for practice on your own before running the challenge. The three puzzles are: Framework Puzzle : a grid resembling a crossword, but instead of clues, you're provided with a list of scrambled words. Your goal is to fit these words into the grid, unscrambling them as you go. Numbrix Puzzle : consists of a grid of numbers. The goal is to fill in the grid with numbers in sequential order, starting from 1 and ending at the highest number given. Each number must be adjacent to the previous or next number in sequence, either horizontally or vertically. Some Numbers will be given to start the puzzle to guide your solve. Drop Quote Puzzle : a grid of squares and a set of given letters which “drop” into the grid. When the puzzle is solved, You will have a phrase of some kind. Within the grid, black boxes represent the spaces between words. some words may be broken between lines, starting at the end of one line and continuing to the beginning of the next line — words only end at black boxes or the end of the puzzle. The given letters at the bottom of a drop quote puzzle are organized by the column they “drop” into, and are given in alphabetical order. (edited) 4:13 PM The rules for the challenge are very straight forward: Enter the command !F5-Empty-Space (This will give you the google sheets page, MAKE A COPY) Solve each tabs Puzzle and send a screenshot for proof Solve the three Hidden Codes and enter them on the cover page to reveal the logo then send a screenshot of the completed cover page! Challenge will be due at Wednesday, November 6, 2024 8:00 PM if you have any questions please ping me in your submissions. KawaiiQuack 11/5/2024 7:23 PM @snazztastic human beings welcome to the mandatory Dicy challenge Dicy 11/6/2024 8:01 PM @Kireina @All Updates I have some results 8:01 PM Ill make them quick tonight 8:01 PM in 5th place 8:01 PM Cinnanmon with a DNF 8:02 PM next in 4th place with a time of 1:09:39 1 8:02 PM Pigeon 8:02 PM but not much quicker in 3rd place 8:03 PM with a time of 1:04:28 1 8:03 PM LN 8:03 PM now our top two were both a bit faster 8:03 PM both doing well under an hour 8:03 PM but who wins tyler or willow 8:04 PM with a time of..... 21:26 8:04 PM @3rd-Willow has won induvial immunity over Tylers 34:11 Exported 18 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

archive / f6-immunity-challenge Cwiski 10/11/2024 7:22 AM F6: Rankings and Queens Hey y’all! Who’s ready for their second Cwis challenge of the season? So for this challenge, I drew inspiration from a jackbox game that some of y’all might be familiar with, it’s called Quixort . Here’s how todays challenge will work: Upon entering the command, you will be given 3 questions/prompts about the season, as well as their answers. Your goal for each prompt is to rank the answers in the correct order. An example prompt would look like this: Order the planets in our solar system from closest to furthest from the sun: Earth, Jupiter, Mars, Mercury, Neptune, Saturn, Uranus, Venus For simplicity sake and using the example above, I ask that you input your answers as such: Prompt 1: 1. Mercury 2. Venus 3. Earth 4. Mars 5. Jupiter 6. Saturn 7. Uranus 8. Neptune With a potential total of 30 points, you will earn one point per correct placement, and the castaway with the most prompts correctly placed will win individual immunity (with tiebreaker coming down to who took less time to submit from entering the command) Should there be any ties while ranking, the placement of the items within the tie do not matter. Hope that’s simple enough! Keep in mind that when you enter the command you will be given all 3 prompts at once, so plan your time accordingly. The command is "?f6-rank" Good luck and have fun (edited) Cwiski 11/3/2024 7:43 PM @Kireina Another Cwis Challenge! Go nuts and ping if you have any questions Cwiski 11/3/2024 8:01 PM Also no discussion of the challenge please and thank you! Cwiski 11/4/2024 6:27 PM @Kireina @All Updates who wants some early results?? 6:27 PM I do because I’m at the gym! 6:28 PM A small note: I made an Oopsie and didn’t establish that only the losing tribe attended f12 tribal, so there are different answers allowed for prompt 1, but it didn’t affect the overall outcome 6:28 PM ANYWAYS LETS DO IT 6:28 PM in 6th place is @3rd-Willow with 10/30 6:29 PM In 5th is @5th-Cinnamon with 22/30 6:29 PM In 4th is @2nd-Pigeon with 25/30 6:29 PM In 3rd is @1st-LN with 29/30 6:30 PM Meaning our two remaining players, @6th-IzzyB and @4th-Tyler both scored a 30/30! So it comes down to time 6:30 PM Izzy got a time of 23:48 6:30 PM Was Tyler able to beat that? 6:30 PM They… 6:30 PM . 6:30 PM . 6:30 PM . 6:31 PM Did! With a time of 19:26, @4th-Tyler wins immunity! 6:31 PM Congrats Tyler, if anyone has questions about your scores feel free to ask and I will get back to you after the gym Exported 20 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

archive / f7-immunity-challenge Austin 11/1/2024 1:38 PM Woooo Austin challenge number 2!!! I know you guys missed me and my overly complicated way of things! 1:38 PM Today we have 1:38 PM # Gauntlet Games! 1:38 PM Here’s how it will work: In this challenge, you’ll face a series of rounds designed to test different skills. Each of you will complete all four parts of the challenge, but only those who survive each round will have their scores counted for the following rounds. If you’re eliminated in a round, your scores in later rounds won’t matter. You won’t know until the end at results! The details of each challenge will be revealed as you begin each one. So, stay sharp and give each round your best effort—your immunity is on the line! Here’s an outline: • Round 1: The two lowest scores/times will be eliminated, leaving 5 players eligible for the next round. • Round 2: The two lowest scores/times will be eliminated from the 5 eligible, leaving 3 players eligible for the next round. • Final Round: The player with the best time/score, between the 3 eligible people, will win individual immunity! Everyone will complete all rounds, but only the remaining eligible players’ scores will be considered each time. Best of luck—let’s see who can adapt and conquer! First command- ?challenge-1 Second Command- ?challenge-2 Their Command- ?challenge-3 Finish each challenge before starting the next! Also you will be timed from the time you put in the command so be ready! Please ping me with questions I know this can be confusing KawaiiQuack 11/1/2024 7:29 PM @snazztastic human beings just in case you did not see it Austin 11/2/2024 7:07 PM Wooo 7:07 PM Who’s ready for results!!! 7:11 PM Next up is Cinnamon 7:11 PM Who sadly had a DNF 7:11 PM So we have our first eliminated 7:11 PM Next up is Pigeon 7:12 PM Needs to beat Willows score of 88 to survive 7:12 PM And they did!!! 7:12 PM With 67 7:12 PM Now it’s down to Willow vs Izzy 7:12 PM Izzy needs to beat 88 7:12 PM She did 7:12 PM NOT 7:13 PM With a score of 92 7:13 PM So our next 5 move onto WiKi race 7:13 PM Let’s start off with 7:13 PM Tyler 7:13 PM Who got a respectable time of 7:14 PM 17 seconds!!!! 2 7:14 PM Yes that’s right 7:14 PM Next up is Willow 7:15 PM Barely surviving last round 7:15 PM Got a time of 2:10 7:15 PM Doesn’t beat Tyler 7:15 PM How surprising 7:15 PM Next we have 7:15 PM LN 7:16 PM Who got a time of 5 minutes 7:16 PM Now we have pigeon 7:17 PM Who got a time of 1:01 7:17 PM Which means LN has been eliminated 7:17 PM Now it’s down to Brett… and Willow once again 7:17 PM Brett needs to beat a time of 2:10 7:17 PM He got 7:18 PM 3:11 7:18 PM Which means he’s eliminated and Willow moves onto the final round!!! archive / f8-immunity-challenge Cwiski 10/8/2024 7:14 PM F8: Time to Game! Guys I'm going to keep this short, sweet, and to the point: I love to game! Whether it be singleplayer or with friends, I am a gamer at heart! With this, I figured I would share my love of gaming with all of you, and have you compete in a gaming challenge! Isn't that so fun??? Last season I ran a speedrunning challenge, and this season I thought I’d do the opposite. Let’s take our time here, shall we? The challenge is simple: when you're ready you will enter the command "?f8-gamer" into your submissions channel. Upon entering the command, you will receive the link to the game you will be playing. The moment the command is entered, you will have 1 hour to achieve the highest score possbile you can in said game. The player who records the highest score will be the winner of individual immunity, with tiebreakers coming down to who submitted their score fastest within that hour timeframe. You may submit as many scores as you'd like within the hour, and we will be taking the highest score you submit! It's as simple as that! Good luck gamers (edited) Cwiski 10/29/2024 7:21 PM @Kireina @All Updates cwis challenge! go nuts Cwiski 10/29/2024 7:33 PM Reminder not to discuss the challenge/selected game with anyone Cwiski 10/30/2024 2:32 PM @Kireina sorry for the ping As per request, will be extending the challenge a bit. The latest you can run the command is 8:00pm EST, meaning results will come out around 9:00pm EST Cwiski 10/30/2024 9:00 PM @Kireina @All Updates and that’s time! Let’s move through this quickly so I can watch the Yankee game 9:01 PM In 8th place is Cinnamon with 4 In 7th place is Alba with 25 In 6th place is IzzyB with 35 9:01 PM In 5th is pigeon with 53 9:02 PM Just ahead with 59 is Tyler in 4th 9:02 PM Down to the top 3! Wow! So crazy! 9:02 PM Getting the bronze medal is LN with a score of 64 9:03 PM Leaving us with @Brett and @Willow vying for 1st and 2nd 9:03 PM Willow netted a score of 71 but was that enough to beat Brett? 9:03 PM It 9:03 PM . 9:03 PM . 9:03 PM . 9:04 PM Was not! As Brett earns immunity with a solid score of 96. Congrats @Brett ! To tribal with the rest of you thank you for playing my funky game Exported 17 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

archive / f9-immunity-challenge Armuski 10/27/2024 6:34 PM F9: Beyond the stars! For this challenge, you'll be doing a few mini challenges! You can pick as many as you want, ranging in difficulty from 1-12. For every challenge you do, you get an amount of points, that being the amount that was stated on the difficulty. So if you were to do challenge nine, you would get nine points by completing it! If you were to FAIL a challenge however, you lose half of the points of that challenge AND any challenges you do afterwards will not count for your total. Let's say Aunder is doing their thing. They complete challenge one, three, and five. They sit at a pretty nine points. They feel cocky and go for challenge 12, but lose. That means they lose six points, and their challenge ends with him getting 3 points total. You can do them in any order you'd like, so feel free to start wherever you'd like! I heavily encourage having some sort of editing software on hand. The command for the challenges are "?planet-x" where x is the difficulty. I know me dreya and pichu will stick together but I'm not sure whats going on with the other side of the tribe 9:02 AM well, actually, i don't mean "side". i told izzy during the last tribal that i think this tribe has the devil in it is split into two sides: me, dreya, and pichu vs theo, dar, and alba. obviously with theo getting votes from both dar and alba that was an incorrect read from me. i just hope izzy doesn't try to gang the duo up against my group now that i kind of dropped the fact im working with dreya and pichu on her 9:03 AM i do feel like i can trust izzy, at least a great deal more than on lilly, but we really dont have a working relationship and its likely never going to get to that point. so the best i can do is stay on her good side. 9:04 AM another thing, now that all the theo nonsense is done, we cannot lose anymore lillys. We are now down 8-5, and thats gonna be a huge problem especially if we merge sooner than expected. 9:08 AM In a perfect world we could just go back to what dreya wants and just get rid of dar as swiftly as we did with theo if we lose, but dar did stand by his word and vote theo, so he's earned a decent amount of my trust back. ill vote dar if i absolutely have too but id much rather alba goes, not sure how to make it happen though. 11th-Nate 10/19/2024 7:32 PM thing is 7:32 PM i feel like everyone here agrees a kaya needs to go here 7:32 PM so i might be able to be a bit blunt with dar if he pushes me 7:32 PM if he doesnt give any ideas im just gonna tell him alba Homie-Bot BOT 10/19/2024 8:21 PM 1. What is your favorite video game? 2. What is your favorite board game? 3. What are your thoughts on tribal? Will you ever stop losing? 4. Give trust rankings (please), mandatory by the end of the episode 11th-Nate 10/19/2024 8:35 PM my favorite video game is guitar hero 3, I love the first two as well but this one includes so many of my all-time favorite songs like raining blood, holiday in cambodia, barracuda, cult of personality, one, paint it black, a lot more 11th-Nate 10/19/2024 10:08 PM #dar-nate I didn't have to go lol 10:09 PM I need Dar to realize I own him in this game 10:09 PM hmm ill do a video confessional 11th-Nate 10/20/2024 12:59 AM Youtube's tweaking out, ill post it tomorrow 12:59 AM except it may now be slightly out of date since we're going for dar now cause pichu says thats what he wants :/ 12:59 AM if it comes down to it, oh well, having my own puppy was fun while it lasted Homie-Bot 1. What is your favorite video game? 2. What is your favorite board game? 3. What are your thoughts on tribal? Will you ever stop losing? 4. Give trust rankings (please), mandatory by the end of the episode 11th-Nate 10/20/2024 1:00 AM pichu dreya izzy dar alba (edited) 11th-Nate 10/20/2024 8:50 AM Izzy's asking about an alliance with a "third party" 8:50 AM and i can just make it so that we keep robloxian high school and just add izzy 8:50 AM im totally fine with her 8:57 AM https://youtu.be/wTZAd8zKCj0?si=1MvO3poHRl6Gpsqk Nathan Marcello Tagtreevivor S2 Video Confessional C 8:57 AM Just pretend i dont wanna keep dar here lmao, i mean i still do but the whole plan shifted last night 11th-Nate 10/20/2024 7:08 PM Sorry dude wish I could keep my lap dog for longer but all good things must come to an end ig 7:10 PM THATS SO CRINGE LOL 7:11 PM You knew I was running things so you waited until you knew you were out to say something? That's such a sissy move Pilot 10/20/2024 7:12 PM 11th-Nate 10/21/2024 2:59 PM uh, wtf? 2:59 PM if i do tell people it's gonna be your ass so i hope pichu does come around 11th-Nate 10/21/2024 7:07 PM I mean what I said to Pichu, I'm not gonna tell people that he doesn't want to vote Alba here. 7:10 PM I'll just ask about the vote in #dar-lies-angels so he has to say it himself, or just be a fish out of water. (edited) Homie-Bot BOT 10/21/2024 7:12 PM 1. How would you describe your perfect day? 2. What is your favorite flower? 3. How will you respond if the person your tribe votes out, doesn't go home tonight? Do you think your tribe will win the challenge? 4. Is there anyone you are hoping does or doesn't get voted out on the other tribe? Who do you expect to go home? 11th-Nate 10/22/2024 2:05 PM Why is Alba coming to me with this emotional paragraph about why Dar was a liar and how she's so grateful I never wrote her name down? 2:06 PM the obvious irony in all of this 2:06 PM Like, I just never had to vote you until now. It was almost you yesterday but Pichu changed my mind, so you should be thanking him not me. 11th-Nate 10/22/2024 3:30 PM so izzy just revealed to me that pichu and alba are both voting for dreya or i 3:30 PM and trying to get her to join 3:30 PM there is no way those two events aren't linked 11th-Nate 10/22/2024 4:15 PM I'm honestly expecting to get voted here, wow 4:17 PM all because pichu doesnt want to vote the obvious person 4:17 PM i feel like at least one of dreya or izzy is being dishonest with me as well 4:19 PM just how fucking stupid do you have to be to not vote the one person not in your alliance 4:19 PM we are literally about to merge it's not exactly a secret 4:20 PM trust: dreya izzy pichu alba 4:20 PM gah i need to punch something 11th-Nate 10/22/2024 6:46 PM #nate-pichu "I know you're stressed and I'm sorry I'm putting you through it" well you're actively choosing to vote me, and you also lied to me about not lobbying with Izzy (you did, she ratted on you asap) 6:46 PM So no, you aren't sorry 6:47 PM bro keeps saying he understands why its stressful even when we all know im not gonna get voted out, but theres seriously no way to actually know that. 6:48 PM jesus 6:48 PM orgs and bipolar do not mix 11th-Nate 10/22/2024 7:09 PM well thats a relief, i dont even gotta pray on winning 7:10 PM good for dreya, and now izzy cause i know for sure i can trust her 7:10 PM sucks for pichu though! (edited) 7:15 PM I guess Alba's staying, which is less than favorable :/ Pilot 10/22/2024 7:28 PM 11th-Nate 10/22/2024 8:02 PM just gonna be completely honest with brett here and tell him the Ilana story 11th-Nate 10/22/2024 8:24 PM #ninja-turtles lemme play a sad song for y'all on the world's smallest violin 8:24 PM so anyways tyler explained to me keira was throwing out 3 names at once so she blew herself up basically 8:24 PM and he's suggesting i get close with LN and Willow 8:24 PM but the former is cluse with Alba so THATS gonna be interesting 11th-Nate 10/24/2024 7:28 AM I died in almost every game greaaat 7:28 AM I don't know if I should or shouldn't be concerned that it seems like everyone rushed to vote me Homie-Bot BOT 10/24/2024 7:20 PM 1. How are you adjusting to the merge? 2. How do you feel about your performance in the challenge? 3. Are you feeling in danger this round? 4. Please give trust rankings of the tribe! This is mandatory and must be done before the end of the episode. 11th-Nate 10/24/2024 8:15 PM So Some interesting news came out for me irl 8:15 PM And I kinda need to stp and go deal with that. 8:15 PM More info soon (probably) 11th-Nate 10/27/2024 7:12 PM Pichu huh 7:13 PM can't say i understand why him but i feel like the events of last tribal would have something to do with it 7:13 PM obviously the other vote for dreya was alba 7:14 PM sucks that pichu is thefirst legit boot of the merge tho, he was in my top 3 to win :/ 11th-Nate 11/3/2024 7:11 PM No comment 7:11 PM I mean I'm happy that a pagonging isn't happening (or at least not completely happening) but Brett is only getting out now because Alba put a target on his back right before she left 7:12 PM Change my view, pinning a target on one's back by saying something AFTER all the votes are read and AFTER you're officially eliminated is THE sissy move 7:14 PM Is the gameplay in this season stupid, yeah it sounds like it from what people are actually helping me understand (so Pichu and no one else) but I personally don't think that's reasoning to be as petty as Alba was Exported 254 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

/ 13th-dar-confessional Pilot 10/4/2024 4:29 PM 13th-Dar 10/4/2024 8:00 PM WELL HELLO HELLO! 8:00 PM 8:01 PM LET ME INTRODUCE MYSELF TO THE AUDIENCE! 8:01 PM I’m DAR, 25 8:01 PM and I’m from Singapore!! 8:02 PM I’m a HUGEEEEEE SWIFTIE! 8:03 PM I love all the main pop girlies. I’m not basic, I just genuinely love them all! 8:03 PM Just saw OLIVIA on Tuesday/Wednesday! ‍ 8:04 PM 8:04 PM 8:04 PM Well ok, aside from MUSIC 8:05 PM I’M ALSO A SURVIVOR, BIG BROTHER, THE TRAITORS & AMAZING RAC FAN! 8:05 PM Was an ANGELEAH stan on BB but ️ 8:06 PM Oh wells! The recent survivor episode boot was ROBBED! 8:07 PM Okay now what I do for a living? Well I’m only an Administrator at my country’s tourist spot! 8:07 PM 8:07 PM If you see this in Singapore, that’s where I work!! 8:07 PM Pretty ain’t it? 8:08 PM Alright now…to be honest I forgot that this game was even starting LOL. Got a good jumpscared when I saw the notification 8:09 PM But now that I’m aware……..let the GAMES fucking begin!!! 8:09 PM Currently am warming up to my new tribe, what I’m good at is being social and if I skate by pre merge and make it to merge, I can go far 8:10 PM I know my game style, I can be messy, I can come off as a threat. But I’m for sure not going down without a fight 8:10 PM First bad impression on my list: WILLOW 8:10 PM for stupid reason 8:11 PM She doesn’t like Taylor 8:11 PM blacklisted! 8:11 PM I’m kidding 8:11 PM I’ll give her a chace. But she’s only 16. I usually don’t do well will people way younger than me 8:12 PM I just think they tend to overplay and be too overly social. If you could instantly become an expert in any random skill, what would it be and why? 2. Have you ever accidentally sent a text to the wrong person? What happened? 3. Do you feel in danger of being voted out here? 4. How good do you think your chances are of winning the game? 13th-Dar 10/18/2024 11:22 AM 1. I wanna be able to sing. I think being a performer looks so fun and rewarding at the same time. 2. Hmmmmmmmm not that i recalled off 3. To be honest. I should be nervous. If I’m not then there’s something wrong. After showing my cards last tribal it’s definitely going to be a trickey spot for me. 4. If I can survive this tribal and then run the merge, I know I can win this. I already had my first drop from a roller coaster ride and that’s going to be a good start to a happy ending story. 11:23 AM This tribal. Theo theo theo. Idc what happens, as long as it is not me. I’m good. I’ve entered my self preservation mode. It’s all about survival right now. 13th-Dar 10/18/2024 7:09 PM Final 13!! Pilot 10/18/2024 7:10 PM 13th-Dar 10/19/2024 5:49 PM THIS CHALLENGE 5:49 PM is testing my patience 5:49 PM I can’t think of anything with the drawing that was given 5:49 PM Ok ya some I’m probably am correct 5:49 PM but….? huh Homie-Bot BOT 10/19/2024 8:21 PM 1. What is your favorite video game? 2. What is your favorite board game? 3. What are your thoughts on tribal? Will you ever stop losing? 4. Give trust rankings (please), mandatory by the end of the episode 13th-Dar 10/19/2024 9:52 PM Lol nate is acting all smart 9:53 PM and trying to question my knowledge on survivor?? 9:53 PM Im just going to suck up right now 9:54 PM UGH they want to get rid of Alba 9:54 PM I’M NOT HAVING IT 9:54 PM but what else can I do? 9:55 PM if Alba is the sacrifise here 9:55 PM Yall know what 9:55 PM It’s making me more valuable 9:55 PM when i merge 9:55 PM ALONE 9:55 PM running back to my OGs 9:55 PM THROW Pichu / Nate / Dreya under the bus 9:56 PM Take their asses out one by one 9:56 PM And work on my relation ships with the OGs and 9:56 PM just go far 10:02 PM I’m begging 10:02 PM the survivor gods 10:02 PM pls be merge next 10:02 PM Idc if the next round it isn’t going to be a juror 10:02 PM I want to MERGE 10:02 PM 10:03 PM I’ve never been so desperate to get out of a situation 10:03 PM I can’t wait to make Pichu look sooooo bad 10:03 PM I can’t wait to get people viewing Nate and Dreya as the top dogs 10:03 PM I can’t wait to see their asses get voted out 10:03 PM Especially Nate. 10:03 PM I just can’t wait 10:05 PM RIDI FUCKING CULOUS. 10:05 PM Close enough, welcome back Rome. 10:07 PM They are cornering me 10:07 PM and not giving me a fucking say 10:08 PM Ok Nate, you get your fucking WAY now 10:08 PM NOT FOR LONG YOU IDIOT. 13th-Dar 10/20/2024 12:55 AM OOP- is this something that I can work with to potentially flip the votes? 12:55 AM i was not lying. 12:56 AM ️pls turn on one another ️ 13th-Dar 10/20/2024 10:28 AM So um 10:28 AM Pichu wanna vote for Izzy 10:28 AM and go for a tie for Alba 10:28 AM Thinks that Nate/Dreya wouldn’t got for rocks for Izzy 10:29 AM I’m here for it honestly (edited) 10:29 AM I feel bad lol 10:29 AM I just spoke to Izzy about having her back 10:29 AM At this point, I’m playing all their games. but don’t count me out at merge. 10:30 AM I have my bullets locked and loaded 10:30 AM I’m just waiting for the right time to strike and not miss 10:30 AM I’m cringing at the way I’m speaking to all these kids 10:30 AM Well im not too far of age from them but it still feel like im old. 10:31 AM I kinda miss talking to Willow Keira and Cinnamon 10:31 AM Lol 10:31 AM As much as I do not want LN to go far…i’ll include him on the tea and gain his trust 10:32 AM I want to be that person where they get the info from but never viewed as a target but rather a number 10:33 AM Ngl! coming into this season, i thought i will be more loud than what im doing now 10:34 AM I hope im the main character for each of the episodes 10:35 AM 10:35 AM failed a blindside, picking myself back up, a reason for the tie this tribal 10:36 AM isnt that main character hehe 10:37 AM with that being said 10:37 AM stream APT. 10:37 AM 10:37 AM WHAT A BOP!!!! Super obvious meta that I see Brett doing rn, trying to open conversation about tribal without saying any strategy. This is pretty risky though as I want to be part of hearing the first name at the first tribal which always seems to stick and have a lasting impact. Praying to god it’s not me 7:44 PM One problem is my patience. Brett is definitely gonna out patient me in terms of not talking strategy soooo if I do the voting early meta maybeee that’ll give me an excuse 7:44 PM I don’t wanna do it when I just started talking to people though 7:45 PM I’ll give it a little bit 17th-GScrub 10/6/2024 8:34 PM Alright im submitting early vote now 8:34 PM Derek just got on so this could be setting him up heheh Homie-Bot Hi! Please rank your tribe mates from 1-9, with 1 being the person you trust most, and 9 being the person you trust least, this MUST be done before 10/7/2024 7:00 PM 17th-GScrub 10/6/2024 8:39 PM ------- Okay ill answer these ez questions for now My favorite color is green ong but I also love orange If I could have anyyy animal as a pet it would probably be big foot. I would force him to tell me all of his secrets Mehhh. This tribe is pretty lame. I felt like I hadnt done as much as I could socially and I also felt like I was on the bottom. It was clear to me that people thought I didnt give a great performance in the first challenge based on Brandy voting me and saying so, and there were some people I didnt even get to talk about the vote the first tribal which is pretty bad. I always like to include everyone on the vote because if some dickhead voted before talking to me about it I like cant trust them. This tribal being automatic kinda sucked for me because I wanted to show a better effort in the second challenge and maybe avoid a tribal before the easy votes started to run out. I do love double tribals though because they speed up the game and allow you to the dynamics of both tribes if one wins every challenge. In the start of tribal, Brett was the first person I talked strategy with. He usually is because Ive talked to him the most and am most comfortable with him. I am though definitely aware of his threat level and how dangerous he is socially and likely strategically. If the opportunity comes to take him out I would take it before it becomes too late. However, that was unlikely to happen quick, which is exactly why its a good idea to remain his ally for a little while. Brett told me that Theo had supposedly thrown out Etay's name. I was revealed by this idea because I hadnt talked much to Etay, and it would be someone that wasnt me. So I then talked to Theo. Theo told me that he had no idea who to vote. This was an immediate red flag to me and got me extremely paranoid. I had assumed that this tribal would be an uphill battle and I would have to cause chaos or fight to stay in the game, and this verified to me that at least one of Theo/Brett was lying to me 5:24 PM I knew I would have to make a move. Theo to me was pretty dry and straightforward with strategy, so if I wanted to get information or flip someone with ease, I knew I would be best off trying something with him. So I came up with a plan to tell Theo that someone had told me that Theo had been spreading my name, and I wouldnt tell Theo who said this until either he admitted it or I was safe after tribal. This plan was a pretty last resort risky type plan, but I really felt like I had nothing else to do. Theo quickly replied to me asking who said it, and he mentioned both that he was thinking Etay for the vote, and that he thought I had actually put in a good performance in the first challenge. While Theo was telling me this, Brett messaged me saying "lets try not to have too much drama this tribal". Soooo I may have overreacted a littttle bit. I believed that Theo actually did want Etay out, but he was just being cautious in telling me about it at first. But... Brett clearly had heard from Theo what I was telling him. This let me believe that Theo and Brett were extremely close. It made sense to me because Theo seemed to have low standards for people he trusted, especially people who talk a lot, and Brett was the most active member on the tribe. Despite the mistake in having too much paranoia, I was still able to manage to flip this into a good move. I told Theo that I believed him now and that the person who told me this I thought was actually just trying to cause chaos. Without me having to propose it myself, Theo proposed that I tell him who said all of this after tribal if it were a simple unanimous Etay vote. So the next day, I talked to everyone and they all agreed that it should be a simple Etay unanimous vote, and that it was being spread around by the whole tribe. Etay had talked to me and told me that he simply wanted Theo out. 5:24 PM The only person to talk to was Brett. I knew I had to come up with something to tell him because I suspected that Theo had told him all I had told Theo. I would try to make the story like up perfectly with what I told to Theo. Brett told me that Etay had also told him Theo's name, and that Etay had heard Theo was spreading his name. So, I made up the lie that Etay had told me Theo told him that Theo wanted me out. This would create a scapegoat for this lie I made up to get information from Theo, and I would tell it to Brett first so he would think he has my trust. Me and Brett both agreed it could be a simple Etay vote. After this, I talked to Theo and told him that it was actually Etay who was just trying to cause chaos to save himself. Etay was voted out unanimously 8-1. I think ultimately that’s the best way for me to not break my promise for her. 6:48 AM POWER RANKINGS: 1. LN 2. Tyler 3. Willow 4. Cinnamon 5. Izzy 6. Pigeon 7th-Brett 11/3/2024 10:29 AM bruh izzy is so lame lol 10:30 AM and why are people in the game continually listening to her when shes had nothing to lose since we merged basically 10:30 AM while i do think a tyler/me/ln ftc is best for me i sure as hell never said that 10:32 AM i swear if that caused me to go out due to pigeon or willow flipping 10:32 AM and ln played the swop 10:32 AM i will lose my mind 7th-Brett 11/3/2024 11:14 AM i just gotta keep calm and have faith in my allies 7th-Brett 11/3/2024 5:02 PM I’m being real I think I’m so cooked 5:03 PM I think pigeon is gonna flip and because of the vote pearl it’s gonna result in a 3- 3 2 against me and send me home 5:03 PM If that’s the case I’ll feel so robbed I can’t lie 5:03 PM The SWOP play is coming back to bite us hard 5:03 PM And there’s nothing I can do besides pray pigeon is with us 7th-Brett 11/11/2024 1:59 AM I’m not perfect, I’ve absolutely made my mistakes (edited) 1:59 AM but I expected more out of LN here (edited) 2:00 AM you played far and away the best game out of the final three but Willow is killing the questions she’s gotten 2:00 AM Again, no hard feelings at all. I think you’re a good guy and I like to think that we’ve become friends 2:00 AM But on a game level, I’m absolutely baffled 7th-Brett 11/11/2024 3:10 PM Watch him win and me get clown reacted LOL 7th-Brett 11/11/2024 4:03 PM I’ve come around on him 4:03 PM Chat I may be changing my vote… 7th-Brett 11/11/2024 7:26 PM Update I did lol 1 Exported 697 message(s) Timezone: UTC-5

Each of you must submit a vote to eliminate one of your fellow tribemates in your submissions channel by the deadline tomorrow. You may change your vote as many times you would like up until the deadline, but once the deadline passes your vote is locked, and can no longer be changed. The deadline to submit your vote is 10/18/2024 7:00 PM 20 minutes before the deadline, we will begin live Tribal Council, where a member of Production will ask you questions about the game and your experience thus far. When the deadline hits, the live advantage period will begin. You will have 5 minutes to play any advantages you may have found. If you wish to play an advantage but will not be online at this time, you may pre-play it in your submissions channel and we will play it for you. To submit your vote, use any image-editing software to write or type the player's name on our parchment, then send it in your submissions channel. You may decorate your parchment, but make sure it is clear who you are voting for. Theo will be spectating this tribal, and will join the tribe after the vote. / f16-lilly-tribal Pilot 10/12/2024 5:20 PM In about 24 hours from now, one of you might become the 5th person voted out of Tagtreevivor Planet Muski. Each of you must submit a vote to eliminate one of your fellow tribemates in your submissions channel by the deadline tomorrow. You may change your vote as many times you would like up until the deadline, but once the deadline passes your vote is locked, and can no longer be changed. The deadline to submit your vote is 10/13/2024 7:00 PM 20 minutes before the deadline, we will begin live Tribal Council, where a member of Production will ask you questions about the game and your experience thus far. When the deadline hits, the live advantage period will begin. You will have 5 minutes to play any advantages you may have found. If you wish to play an advantage but will not be online at this time, you may pre-play it in your submissions channel and we will play it for you. To submit your vote, use any image-editing software to write or type the player's name on our parchment, then send it in your submissions channel. You may decorate your parchment, but make sure it is clear who you are voting for. If you have any questions, please ask 5:20 PM 5:21 PM !parchment Pilot !parchment Homie-Bot BOT 10/12/2024 5:21 PM 9th-Dreya 10/12/2024 6:19 PM grrr 4th-Tyler 10/12/2024 8:38 PM I will try and talk to yall more tomorrow. Aunder 10/13/2024 6:40 PM @Lilly @Tribal Updates @All Updates hiiiiii 7th-Brett 10/13/2024 6:40 PM hi there 14th-Theo 10/13/2024 6:40 PM Hey Aunder 10/13/2024 6:41 PM How is everyone this fine Tribal evening :) 6:41 PM Ready to vote someone off! 6:41 PM Or not... 6:41 PM Only the next 30 minutes will tell! 6:42 PM @7th-Brett thanks for popping in! Each of you must submit a vote to eliminate one of your fellow tribemates in your submissions channel by the deadline tomorrow. If you wish to play an advantage but will not be online at this time, you may pre-play it in your submissions channel and we will play it for you. / f20-lilly-tribal Pilot 10/6/2024 6:52 PM In about 24 hours from now, one of you will become the 1st person voted out of Tagtreevivor Planet Muski. Each of you must submit a vote to eliminate one of your fellow tribemates in your submissions channel by the deadline tomorrow. You may change your vote as many times you would like up until the deadline, but once the deadline passes your vote is locked, and can no longer be changed. The deadline to submit your vote is 10/7/2024 7:00 PM 20 minutes before the deadline, we will begin live Tribal Council, where a member of Production will ask you questions about the game and your experience thus far. When the deadline hits, the live advantage period will begin. You will have 5 minutes to play any advantages you may have found. If you wish to play an advantage but will not be online at this time, you may pre-play it in your submissions channel and we will play it for you. To submit your vote, use any image-editing software to write or type the player's name on our parchment, then send it in your submissions channel. You may decorate your parchment, but make sure it is clear who you are voting for.
